Explanation:
This infrastructure is designed to scale the system by separating components and improving availability.

A user connects to www.foobar.com through the Internet. The request is handled by a load balancer cluster (HAProxy), which consists of two load balancers in an Active-Active setup. This improves availability and removes a single point of failure.

The load balancers distribute traffic to a dedicated web server. The web server (Nginx) handles incoming HTTP requests and serves static content or forwards requests to the application server.

The application server processes the business logic and interacts with the application code.

The database is placed on a separate server (MySQL). This allows better performance, scalability, and easier management.

Why added components:
Separating the web server, application server, and database improves performance and scalability.
Using two load balancers increases reliability and prevents downtime if one fails.

Application server vs web server:
The web server (Nginx) handles HTTP requests and serves static files.
The application server processes logic, executes code, and interacts with the database.
